profile.aboutUs: Combain is a world leading geolocation service provider for connected IoT devices. Combain has one of the world's largest positioning databases that is used for accurate indoor and outdoor positioning. Combain's customers are leading mobile network operators, national security agencies, tracking device and IoT device manufacturers. The positioning is provided as a cloud-based and onprem API, Combain Location API, as an indoor positioning solution, Combain Indoor, and as a cloud-based IoT tracking platform, Traxmate. Combain is located in Lund, Sweden and in Palo Alto, USA and serves customers worldwide.

exhibition.sustainabilityMotivation: Perstorp has a strong focus on putting forward products which enables customers early in the value chain to shift to sustainable raw materials. profile.aboutUs:
At Perstorp, we believe in improving everyday life ‚Äì making it safer, more convenient and more environmentally sound for billions of people all over the world. 

As a world leading specialty chemicals company, focusing on the global Resins & Coatings, Engineered Fluids and Animal Nutrition markets, our innovative solutions provide essential properties for products used everywhere, every day. Our products can be found in everything ‚Äì from your car and mobile phone to towering wind turbines and the local dairy farm. Put simply, we work to make good products even better, with a clear sustainability agenda. 

Founded in Sweden in 1881, our focused innovation builds on more than 140 years of experience, representing a complete chain of solutions in organic chemistry, process technology and application development.

profile.aboutUs:
MAN Energy Solutions is the world's leading designer of engines for the maritime industry. More than 250 years of experience in advanced engineering of complex systems has prepared us well for our biggest challenge yet: Moving big things to zero.

Our focus is on solutions within sustainable energy, alternative fuels and environmentally friendly technologies. Key parts of our strategy is Digitalization and Decarbonization, and with this we innovate and demonstrate continues market leading technologies, e.g. dual fuel- and low-emission solutions. We move the boundaries and set the tone for the maritime operational-, energy and emission targets of the future.

We engineer systems for deep decarbonization in sectors that matter most.
We make a virtue out of creating sustainable solutions and contribute to a carbon neutral economy.
We have over 15,000 employees worldwide.
profile.didYouKnow:
That our team in Denmark consists of over 2.200 employees with more than 40 nationalities, and we offer a wide range of job opportunities for everyone, from student assistants to PhDs, flexible jobs, graduates, and full-time positions. We are proud of our diverse team and recognize that our differences make us stronger. We believe that a culture of diversity and inclusion is critical to our success and enables us to think outside the box, develop innovative solutions, and meet the diverse needs of our customers.

At MAN Energy Solutions, we are committed to providing equal opportunities for everyone and promoting equal treatment in our workplace. We aim to foster a culture that is fair, unprejudiced, and open-minded, where everyone can feel comfortable being themselves and contributing to our collective success.

If you are seeking a workplace that values diversity and inclusivity, we invite you to join our team at MAN Energy Solutions. We are committed to building a culture of diversity and inclusion that enables us to reach our full potential and achieve our goals together.
profile.name: MAN Energy Solutions

profile.aboutUs:
Application and Network Intelligence
As network and application usage shifts on a daily basis, service providers are looking for new ways to analyze, optimize, and monetize applications so they can deliver high quality consumer and enterprise experiences. This requires changes on three critical fronts:

 

Maintaining accurate visibility of application and network traffic
Encryption renders most existing data collection methods ineffective. As the Internet continues to go dark, a new approach is needed to maintain a high-level of application and network intelligence, but also to ensure accurate charging and sustained profitability for highly valuable services.

 

Understanding contextual application Quality of Experience
Running a profitable network requires a deep understanding of how critical applications, such as video, gaming, social sharing, and enterprise applications are performing. However, most service providers lack the context and the associated key performance indicators needed to truly determine application quality of experience (QoE).

 

Scaling to meet performance and volumetric requirements
As video shifts to HD and 4K streaming, cloud gaming grows in popularity, and new smart workplace and industry applications gain traction, bandwidth usage is exploding with little additional revenues. Meeting this challenge on the data plane requires hyper-scalable software solutions optimized to run in flexible cloud, virtual, and physical deployment models.


Sandvine‚Äôs cloud-based Application and Network Intelligence portfolio and pre-packaged use cases help customers analyze, optimize, and monetize application experiences using contextual machine learning-based insights and real-time actions. Market-leading classification of more than 95% of traffic in real time across mobile and fixed networks by user, application, device, and location significantly enhances interactions between users and applications.

 

Sandvine is deployed by over 200 of the largest service providers globally, serving over 2.5 billion users in more than 100 countries. These service providers choose Sandvine on a daily basis for the following reasons:

 

Global Internet Authority 
The leading authority on the continuously evolving internet phenomena dominating global networks


Application and Network Intelligence-Based Solutions
Combines unparalleled application visibility with contextual awareness to deliver complete and comprehensive solutions in key areas: Video, Gaming, Social Sharing, Enterprise Managed Services, and Internet of Things


Best Real-Time Application and Network Data for Inline Actions
Real-time, high-definition granularity with the industry‚Äôs most accurate application classification


Single Pane of Glass 
Sandvine‚Äôs Application and Network Intelligence (ANI) Portal visualizes contextual data, and provides unique application and network QoE scoring metrics critical for improving performance


Proven Leadership for Real-Time Actions
Trusted for over 20 years in large scale communications networks as the ‚Äòinternal engine‚Äô for intelligent policy control and mitigation


Analytics-Driven Automation 
Automation-based use cases drive decisions and actions in a closed-loop cycle, and deliver operational savings and improved efficiency to solve current and future application and network challenges
profile.name: Sandvine

exhibition.sustainabilityMotivation: RWE is a German multinational energy company with global operations, leading the way to a green energy world. RWE Renewables has operated on the Nordic market since March 2018.  Sweden is a key market for the expansion of renewable energy and we are also expanding in Denmark and Norway. RWE currently operates almost 300 MW wind power in the Nordics, with onshore and offshore wind farms in Sweden and Denmark. In addition to that, the development portfolio has a potential of over 10 GW.
exhibition.remarks: Last year we were also in the green zone but became targeted durign demonstrations outside the event. If you would like to further discuss the subject please don't hesitate in reaching out to our contact person Karin Vandenborre.

profile.aboutUs:
RWE, with a history of 125 years in the energy industry, is one of the world's largest energy producers with operations around the globe. With an earlier focus on fossil fuels, RWE has embarked on a major transition of the company towards becoming a pure renewable company. This journey was accelerated in 2021 where the ‚ÄúGrowing Green‚Äù strategy was launched, where RWE will invest 500 billion SEK in renewable technologies towards 2030. 

RWE Renewables is the entity of RWE driving the transition focusing on developing, constructing and operating renewable assets across a variety of technologies; offshore wind, onshore wind, solar PV, battery and hydrogen. 

In the Nordic countries, RWE Renewables are running operations for more than 1 GW of onshore and offshore wind capacity. RWE Renewables has for many years been a leading player in onshore wind. We are also a front runner in offshore wind, where we are constructing Thor in Denmark, the largest offshore wind farm in the Nordic countries, and are in the late development stage of another significant offshore wind farm project in Sweden, S√∂dra Victoria.
profile.name: RWE Renewables Sweden AB

events.description_climate:
We Package Life‚Äôs Everyday Moments for a Renewable Future. 
Packaging touches our everyday lives in so many ways. It keeps our breakfast cereal fresh. It holds the hot tea or coffee that helps get us moving in the morning. It preserves the ready-to-cook evening meal that allows us more time with friends or family. And it holds and protects a host of beauty, healthcare, and other consumer products that we use daily. Our solutions make every part of the day easier, safer, and more convenient.
Yet, packaging is nowadays put under lots of scrutiny. Consumers are insisting that products ‚Äì and the packaging that protects them ‚Äì come from a company they trust and that reflects their values. At the same time, brands and retailers are looking to advance their ESG initiatives. Solving these packaging challenges is our top priority.
Our products start with recycled fibers or virgin fibers from renewable materials. We innovate to support the development of recyclable packaging solutions so we can play our part in the circular economy. All with the aim of building a renewable future for generations to come.

profile.aboutUs:
At Graphic Packaging International, we produce the paper cup that held your coffee this morning, the basket that transported those bottles of craft beer you enjoyed last weekend, and the microwave tray that heated your gourmet meal last night. We‚Äôre one of the largest manufacturers of paperboard and paper-based packaging for some of the world‚Äôs most recognized brands of food, beverage, foodservice, household, personal care and pet care products.


We have over 130 facilities worldwide that provide innovative packaging solutions to help our customers stand out and achieve brand loyalty in a competitive and dynamic marketplace. With a product portfolio that emphasizes renewable, recycled, and recyclable materials, we are as committed to our customers and 24,000 employees as we are to protecting the environment and giving back to the communities where we live and work.


Graphic Packaging International‚Äôs history extends more than 100 years, as numerous legacy companies have joined forces to create an ever-evolving corporation. Despite our name changes over the years, our dedication to innovation, quality, and service never changes.
profile.name: Graphic Packaging International

profile.aboutUs:
Vattenfall is a European energy company with approximately 20,000 employees. For more than 100 years we have electrified industries, supplied energy to people's homes and modernised our way of living through innovation and cooperation.

We are committed to building a future where everyone can choose affordable, fossil-free ways to move, make and live. To succeed we must become fossil free ourselves. But that's not enough. We are looking beyond our own industry to see where we can really make a difference. Together with our partners, we are taking on the responsibility to find new and sustainable ways to electrify transportation, industries and heating.
profile.didYouKnow: Vattenfall has more than 600 different jobs, everything from energy specialist to fish farmers.
profile.name: Vattenfall AB

profile.aboutUs:
ALTEN is one of Europe‚Äôs largest consulting companies within Engineering, IT, and Life Sciences with over 54,000 employees in more than 30 countries. We‚Äôre a global actor with a local presence with 1400 committed colleagues in offices from Lund in the south to Skellefte√• in the north. Our engineers carry out complex and highly technical projects throughout the product development chain of the most prestigious companies in sectors such as Automotive, Aerospace & Defense, Energy, Manufacturing, Public Sector, and Life Sciences. 

For four years in a row, ALTEN has been named one of Sweden's most attractive employers by Karri√§rf√∂retagen, an award for employers that offer unique career and development opportunities.
profile.didYouKnow:
At ALTEN, every individual is equally valuable in building tomorrow‚Äôs world today. We meet future challenges by supporting our clients‚Äô projects and enabling our people to reach their full potential. We do so by offering technological challenges, fulfilling opportunities, inspiring togetherness, and the possibility to contribute to a sustainable future.
We are convinced that your development is driven by your passion. By being active in several different industries, we can offer a wide range of assignments and an opportunity to influence both the world around you and your own development.  With coaching leadership, our leaders will guide you in the right direction. We also offer personalized training opportunities through your individual training budget, which you can use in our internal ALTEN Academy or on external courses.

At ALTEN, there are numerous opportunities to join an inspiring togetherness and do what you enjoy, together with your colleagues. During our Tech Weeks, you get to hear what your colleagues are working on and have a chance to share your own experiences. We have several internal networks, such as ALTEN Sports and Women@ALTEN, where you are given the opportunity to get active with your colleagues or pursue issues and topics that you are passionate about.

At ALTEN, we think it's important to have a balance between work and spare time, which is why we offer three extra days off a year. We have a collective agreement and offer benefits like pension, insurance, and wellness grants.
profile.name: ALTEN

profile.aboutUs: The European Spallation Source is under construction on the outskirts of Lund, a city in southern Sweden. The facility's unique capabilities will both greatly exceed and complement those of today's leading neutron sources, enabling new opportunities for researchers across the spectrum of scientific discovery, including materials and life sciences, energy, environmental technology, cultural heritage and fundamental physics.
profile.didYouKnow: The European Spallation Source is one of the largest science and technology infrastructure projects being built today. The facility design and construction include the most powerful linear proton accelerator ever built, a five-tonne, helium-cooled tungsten target wheel, 22 state-of-the-art neutron instruments, a suite of laboratories, and a supercomputing data management and software development centre. In the context of its history and future as a scientific organisation, however, it is more than the sum of its parts. It is a brand new Big Science organisation, built from the ground up.

profile.aboutUs:
Backer AB develops and brings to market world leading solutions and systems for intelligent heating & control Everyday - Everywhere. We deliver heating systems to private and commercial properties, the automotive industry, MedTech, energy production, process industries and many other applications.

With a production area of over 22 000 m¬≤ We develop the heating solutions our customers need for their product or process. Development is made in tight copoperation with the customer, using our design rules and limitations. Samples and prototypes are made as needed for testing and validation. Finally the full documentation is created, and the industrialization department starts the production.

We are in the reach from Malm√∂, Lund and Copenhagen and you can easily get to us either by car or train. The Backer factory, with its own manufacturing, sourcing, logistics, sales/marketing, and product development in S√∂sdala, is part of the NIBE-group and we head the NIBE Element business area with its 85 sites and 12 000 employees globally.
profile.didYouKnow: Our history began in 1921 when Christian Backer patented today‚Äôs tubular heating element.  In 1949, Backer AB was founded in S√∂sdala, south of H√§ssleholm in Sweden. Still today Backer AB is developing and marketing world class heating solutions in our premisses in S√∂sdala.

exhibition.sustainabilityMotivation: Swegon seeks to continuously improve as a sustainable business when distinguishing and balancing between social, environmental, and economic sustainability, or in other words People, Planet, and Profit. Our products are energy-efficient, and designed to help customers reach their desired indoor climate. Swegon delivers even measurable environmental impact data on its products through Environmental Product Declarations enabling our customers to calculate and reduce a project's carbon footprint. Renewable and fossil-free energy is of course an important part of our strategic focus areas. At the same time, Swegon creates conditions for a sustainable work-life balance to have high levels of well-being, knowing that people who feel good perform better. Not to forget, diversity and inclusion is nothing we are afraid off either.

profile.aboutUs:
VA SYD is one of Sweden's largest water and waste organizations that invests heavily in sustainable wastewater treatment and pushes for environmentally smart solutions in community building. In the industry, we will be one of Europe's most modern and efficient organizations. Our business is open 24/7, has half a million customers and a turnover of more than one billion per year. 
We are in everyone's everyday lives and we are seen in so many different ways; tap water, flush the toilet, take a shower, sort the waste, garden waste and we make room for the water. We are an important player in society.

What do we do? We purify, quality assure and supply drinking water and take care of what is flushed down our sewers to care for the sea and watercourses. We manage rainfall by creating creative solutions for the water's path and collect waste for recycling. We motivate and inspire our customers to make smart environmental choices.

profile.aboutUs:
Preem is Sweden‚Äôs largest fuel company. Our vision is to lead the transition toward a sustainable society. By 2035 Preem will produce 5 million cubic meters of renewable fuels and achieve climate neutrality. 

Our two refineries are among the most modern and environmentally adapted in Europe with a refining capacity of over 18 million cubic meters per year. The business we are in includes trading, production, distribution and sales. We refine and sell fuel, heating and lubricating oil as well as other products to companies and individuals. 

Two thirds of our production are exported are exported to the international market, mainly to north western Europe. We have a nationwide service network with 520 filling stations for private and commercial traffic. Preem AB has around 1,500 employees, of which 1,100 work at our refineries. In 2022, Preem‚Äôs turnover was SEK 161 billion.
profile.didYouKnow:
- Preem is Sweden‚Äôs largest fuel company.
- 2035 at the latest we will have climate-neutral operations with net-zero emissions throughout the value chain. 
- Our refineries in Gothenburg and Lysekil are among the most modern and environmentally friendly refineries in the world. 
- Every day, we supply vital functions with Swedish-produced fuels.
- Two thirds of our production are exported. This means that Preem is one of Sweden's largest export companies.
profile.name: Preem AB

exhibition.sustainabilityMotivation: We believe that renewable electricity is the future and our best way of fighting against climate change. However, for us to rely mostly on renewable electricity fundamental changes to the current electricity power system must take place. And we want to lead this transformation!  At Flower, we operate our Digital Power Refinery Platform also known as a virtual power plant (VPP). To our digital platform, we connect to and control a vast pool of generation, consumption, and storage assets from large-scale industrial facilities to decentralized energy resources which we optimize to produce the most benefit for the electricity system both locally, regionally, and system-wide. We are currently expanding and entering an exciting phase of launching our solutions in new European markets. Currently, we are developing exceptional energy solutions, connecting over 5000 existing assets to our software agnostic platform and we are looking towards the development of the industry to see what comes next!

exhibition.sustainabilityMotivation: What sustainability means to us at Nederman? We are the Clean Air Company and for us sustainability is the core of our business. We are here to protect people, planet and production from the harmful effects of industrial processes. We are inspired by the Sustainability definition to meet the needs of the present without compromising the ability of future generations to meet their own needs. Our sustainability vision is to create a world where industrial air pollution is no longer a threat to human health and our planet. We strive to achieve this through more sustainable and innovative solutions that reduce emissions, promote energy and resource efficiency and by supporting a fair and inclusive society. We aim to bring a holistic approach, balancing economic growth with planetary protection and renewal and ensuring a positive impact on people and societies. That is why we are having a long-term perspective in everything we do.

profile.aboutUs:
At Nordic Sugar Sweden, we work with the sustainable food chain in focus - and to constantly develop new, resource-smart solutions. Our ambition is to have a completely carbon-neutral production by 2045. At our sugar factory in √ñrtofta, we are now finalizing a facility to take fossil-free energy from a nearby heating plant, which from 2022 will mean a direct reduction of fossil energy by up to 25%. A large part of our products are transported by train.
Our sugar beet comes from around 1,000 growers in southern Sweden and our products are sold under the brands Nordic Sugar for industry and Dansukker for consumers. From the residues of sugar production we make high quality animal feed. Nordic Sugar Sweden has an attractive location in the middle of the food region Sk√•ne, just outside the university city Lund, and the company offers good career opportunities. We are part of Nordzucker, one of Europe's leading sugar producers, with a turnover of around ‚Ç¨1.5 billion.
